      <odd id="aspace_f247803468c7596a7198720ce8f9279b">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Additions to this collection will consist of only materials printed or written in the French language, and pertaining to French life and culture. No items or portions of collections will be transferred from individial collections to this collection.</p>  
      </odd>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_98e65d4ff256ed9153a85154d0251f74">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_e11221fbd5ef4de25220392033044f29">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright status for collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_83873fdb417967e2ac486f95b04059a7">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>French Miscellaneous Manuscripts Collection. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_29661a98d87499f1a638da1cc09f37ee">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>An artificial collection of correspondence, manuscripts, volumes, and miscellanea relating to France, 1115-1941.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_c26cf9b0ea38f5adb2b2b0b13f6d42f7">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The papers are arranged in four sections: volumes, correspondence and loose papers, miscellaneous, and oversize. All items that are not listed individually in this register--and this is the vast majority of the papers in the collection--are filed as "correspondence and loose papers in boxes 7-8. Most items are cataloged individually in the manuscript catalog, the union catalog, and the inventory catalog.</p>  
      </arrangement>
